title: Makeup for Uneven Eyelids
content:
CLICK FOR MORE INFO!! Visit http://www.frmheadtotoe.com and follow Jen on twitter at http://twitter.com/frmheadtotoe 

Full blog entry: http://www.frmheadtotoe.com/

My eyes have been uneven a lot lately so I thought I'd do a tutorial for the eye makeup I use when they become asymmetrical. My eyelids are currently dry and pulling weird which is probably why they have been uneven so often! :( Oh, and my crease here isn't very pronounced but the 2 previous days it was a full-on crease and I wanted to do the tutorial before it went away completely. title: Basic Nail Polish Application Tutorial
content:
CLICK FOR MORE INFO!! ---- Visit http://www.frmheadtotoe.com and follow Jen on twitter at http://twitter.com/frmheadtotoe 

Full blog entry here: http://www.frmheadtotoe.com/2010/09/basic-nail-polish-application-tutorial.html

Products mentioned in this video:

* Seche Natural - this is a nail treatment but it works well as a basecoat. I also have and love Seche Clear. 
* OPI Who Needs A Prince? - sheer-ish cute, red-flash pearly pale pink. needs 3 or 4 coats to be opaque, but is SO PRETTY when opaque. 
* Seche Vite - my HG top coat. Basically, this is the magic product that keeps polish on way longer, dries faster, and makes it super shiny. LOVE!

Rings: ebay, small shops, and hubby

title: hello kitty konad nail art tutorial
content:
A tutorial for how to use konad nail art, featuring the Hello Kitty print from plate A02 by GCOCL. I won this plate from a blog giveaway, so I didn't personally buy it but others have found success purchasing from ebay. Visit the blog at http://www.frmheadtotoe.com

polishes:
Zoya Stephanie
Sally Hansen Chrome poilsh in Pink Pearl

You can use non-Konad polishes for stamping, but I find that Konad's Special polishes work best since they are more opaque and dry slower, giving you slightly more time to work. Chrome and holographic polishes look awesome konaded, but dry quickly so you have to work super fast, like in this tutorial. If you work quickly, you can stamp about 3 or 4 fingers before you totally clean the plate again with remover.

Music is Mozart's Divertimento (K131) from http://incompetech.com.

title: TAG: Would You Rather - Beauty Edition
content:
CLICK FOR MORE INFO!! ---- Visit http://www.frmheadtotoe.com and follow Jen on twitter at http://twitter.com/frmheadtotoe 

Full blog entry here: http://www.frmheadtotoe.com/2011/08/tag-would-you-rather-beauty-edition.html

Amarixe: http://youtube.com/amarixe

Nailpolish: Sally Hansen HD polish in Lite
Earrings: Origami butterflys from http://www.shopheqi.com/

----

QUESTIONS:
1.) Would you rather lose all of your mascaras, eyeliners, lipsticks, and lipglosses or lose all of your palettes and eyeshadows?
2.) Would you rather chop off all your hair or never be able to cut it again?
3.) Would you rather have a coral cheek or a pink cheek?
4.) If you had $1000 to spend, would you rather buy clothes or makeup?
5.) Would you rather apply lipstick as eyeliner, or eyeliner as lipstick?
6.) Would you rather only shop at MAC or Sephora?
7.) Would you rather only use one eyeshadow color or one lip color for the rest of your life?
8.) Would you rather wear winter clothes in summer or summer clothes in winter?
9.) Would you rather have dark nails or bright nails all year round?
10.) Would you rather give up your favorite lip product or your favorite eye product?
11.) Would you rather only be able to wear your hair in a ponytail or a messy bun?
12.) Would your rather never be able to paint your nails again or never use lipgloss?
13.) Would you rather shave your eyebrows and have none at all or sharpie them in everyday?
14.) Would you rather live without makeup or nail polish?

title: Natural Beachy Olsen Waves: Remington Air Wave Hair Dryer Review
content:
This is a review of the Remington Air Wave blowdryer. Visit the blog at http://www.frmheadtotoe.com and follow Jen on twitter at http://twitter.com/frmheadtotoe 

Full blog entry here: http://www.frmheadtotoe.com/2010/07/natural-beachy-olsen-waves-remington.html

Many people said this was discontinued but the Remington 3-in-1 hairdryer on has a "beach wave" attachment that does the same thing. People said they found it at Target. :)

This hair dryer with wind tunnel attachment gives you natural beachy waves by spinning your hair around the wind tunnel attachment. The final look gives you an easy, unique look that may be difficult to obtain with curling irons. It reminds me a lot of the Mary Kate and Ashley Olsen's hair!

Products used:
Biosilk Silk Therapy
Remington Air Wave

Earrings are from He Qi Crystal Designs http://hqcdblog.blogspot.com/
Nail polish is Claire's Mood polish in Wild/Calm (I have a video reviewing this polish)

Disclaimer: This product was bought by myself and is in no way affiliated with the company. All my reviews are my 100% honest opinion.

title: New Years Resolutions 2012
content:
CLICK FOR MORE INFO!!  Visit http://www.frmheadtotoe.com and follow Jen on twitter at http://twitter.com/frmheadtotoe 

Full blog entry:
http://www.frmheadtotoe.com/

For books, I've already read The Hunger Games series, Twilight series, Harry Potter series (multiple times), Chronicles of Narnia Series, Charlane Harris (True Blood) vampire series, Ender's Game series, and I also really tend to enjoy socialist fiction like Brave New World, Anthem, and Animal Farm. I do also love young adult novels as long as they are well-written and captivating! :)
